# ProjectFlo — Testing Conventions

## Backend
- Co-locate unit specs with source; name matches the file under test (`quotes.service.ts` → `quotes.service.spec.ts`).
- Use `.e2e-spec.ts` for end-to-end tests.
- Prefer testing service business logic, validation errors, edge cases, and transaction rollback behavior; avoid testing Prisma query-building details.
- Mock Prisma using the repo’s `buildPrisma()` / `buildPrismaTx()` helpers; mock only direct dependencies (not internals of the unit under test).
- For controllers, test guards/param parsing/DTO validation; skip pure delegation tests.
- Assert both happy path and error paths (`NotFoundException`, `BadRequestException`); avoid snapshots for dynamic data.

## Frontend
- No framework is configured yet; when added, use Jest + React Testing Library, co-located `ComponentName.test.tsx`, focusing on user behavior and rendered output.

